snippet.textDisplay: I came back to this after Zeb's masterclass in Mehmaan. The emotion here again is through the roof. You can feel the pain, the longing, the sorrow, the love and the remembrance of a time of peace, togetherness and happiness. It is so beautifully sung. Words aren't enough to do it justice. And Rohail, wow. The composition is so patient, so in line with the emotional core of the song. It realizes that the power of the vocals and sits back, enhancing them to convey their heart. This is how song compositions should be, a sign of someone at the top of their game.
